                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">551.5F1/190: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-16T16:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 16, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 16—12:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>462. As soon as I returned from Paris I consulted with the Foreign Secretary, Sir
                    John Simon, on the issue referred to in the Department’s 331, November 19, 4
                    p.m. Sir John assured me that the proposal would be discussed in the Cabinet,
                    and that subsequently I would be informed. In turn, I shall cable the
                    Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
